            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
                <p>ΒΟ. This is clearly an abbreviation. Found in Borysthenes, such combination of letters immediately calls to mind the city ethnic, as well as the name of 
                the god Boreas who was worshipped at least in Olbia. Is a theonym possible? Personal names in BO are also known...
                In Borysthenes... In Olbia... In Ionia and other Ionian colonies...
                
                Most likely, the text was written on the complete pot, but inscription on a sherd cannot be excluded - the text is centered on the fragment relative 
                to the breaks and there is space left on either side of the letters, telling us that the inscription is fully preserved.</p>
            </div>
